In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney and Chairman of the President's Council of Economic Advisers Alan Krueger discuss the economic importance of extending and expanding the payroll tax cut. Krueger explains that the payroll tax cut has provided important support for the economy, especially during times of economic shocks. He argues that extending and expanding the payroll tax cut is necessary to strengthen and sustain the economic recovery. Krueger also addresses concerns about the impact of extending unemployment benefits and the national debt. Carney also responds to questions about an exemption for Catholic churches, hospitals, and universities from the requirement to cover contraception in insurance plans. He explains that the President is considering the balance between expanding coverage of preventive services and respecting religious beliefs. The briefing ends with Carney commenting on the recent events in Iran and the President's upcoming visit to Scranton, Pennsylvania.